{
  "text": "Peptide fractionation using strong cation exchange. Strong cation exchange (SCX) was used to fractionate the mixed labeled samples as previously described [CITATION_1] . After separation, the 36 fractions collected were combined to yield 10 fractions. These were then vacuum-concentrated, re-suspended and desalted [CITATION_2] .",
